    <section>
      <h2>What ASDLC Is Not</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Not a prompt library.</strong> We don't collect "awesome prompts." We define systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Not a tool recommendation.</strong> Cursor, Claude Code, Windsurf—use what works. The methodology is tool-agnostic.</li>
        <li><strong>Not about replacing developers.</strong> It's about changing <em>what developers do</em>: less typing, more designing.</li>
        <li><strong>Not magic.</strong> Agents are probabilistic. They drift toward mediocrity. ASDLC provides the constraints that keep them useful.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

